# commit-msg policy allowlist
#
# One substring per line. Blank lines and `#` comments ignored.
# A violation is suppressed when ANY allowlisted substring (case-insensitive)
# appears in the offending line.
#
# Use sparingly. Bypass-by-allowlist is auditable in git history;
# bypass-by-`--no-verify` is not. Per CLAUDE.md, every emergency bypass
# also requires a follow-up Issue.
#
# Defaults: filenames of policy docs that legitimately reference vendor
# names. CLAUDE.md is also exempt at the regex level (the catalog uses a
# negative lookahead for `\.md`), but listing the literal here makes the
# exemption visible to humans reviewing this file.

CLAUDE.md
GEMINI.md
GPT.md
docs/references/
